---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Jason Enia - Research & Projects"
  description="Research and current projects by Jason Enia, focusing on the politics of disasters and nuclear weapons."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 md:py-24 px-4">
    <header class="mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <h1
        class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-3"
      >
        Research & Projects
      </h1>
      <p
        class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-normal max-w-2xl leading-tight"
      >
        Uncovering the hidden incentives in politics.
      </p>
      <div class="w-16 h-px bg-rust-500/60 mt-8"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-16">
      <!-- Core Interests Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Core Interests
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <article class="group relative">
              <h3
                class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-4"
              >
                Politics of Nuclear Weapons
              </h3>
              <div
                class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal"
              >
                <p>
                  Analyzing the transaction cost barriers that complicate
                  international cooperation over catastrophic weaponry.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="group relative">
              <h3
                class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-4"
              >
                Politics of Disasters
              </h3>
              <div
                class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal"
              >
                <p>
                  Investigating how political incentives and institutional rules
                  dictate our behavior around major catastrophes.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="group relative">
              <h3
                class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-4"
              >
                Political Economy of Cooperation & Conflict
              </h3>
              <div
                class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal -mb-6"
              >
                <p>
                  Uncovering the strategic ways institutions manage conflict and
                  foster cooperation in an anarchic world.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-t border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10" />

      <!-- Current Book Project Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4 scroll-mt-32" id="book-project">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Current Book Project
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span
              class="block text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500 mb-2"
              >Current Book Project</span
            >
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-1"
            >
              Relative to What?
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light italic mb-6"
            >
              8 Questions That Make You Smarter Every Day
            </p>

            <div
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal space-y-6 prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none"
            >
              <p>
                This book is the culmination of a decade spent teaching research
                methods and 25 years of thinking like an economist. Clarity in
                an increasingly complex world comes from asking better
                questions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Interactive Accordion Section -->
            <div class="mt-16 space-y-16">
              <!-- PART I -->
              <div class="space-y-6">
                <h4
                  class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-6 border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4"
                >
                  Part I: Make the Implicit Explicit
                </h4>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >01.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      How are they measuring that?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    Clarity begins by recognizing that what we think we are
                    measuring isn't always what the data actually reflects. By
                    scrutinizing our definitions and measurement choices, we
                    bridge the gap between our assumptions and the actual
                    evidence.
                  </div>
                </details>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >02.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      Relative to what?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    In isolation, a number or a policy outcome tells us very
                    little. By forcing ourselves to identify the baseline, we
                    uncover the opportunity costs and trade-offs that absolute
                    narratives often hide.
                  </div>
                </details>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >03.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      Is this just one piece—or the whole picture?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    This question forces a critical distinction between a sample
                    and a population. It challenges us to recognize when we are
                    looking at an isolated fragment rather than a representative
                    snapshot of the whole picture.
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>

              <!-- PART II -->
              <div class="space-y-6">
                <h4
                  class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-6 border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4"
                >
                  Part II: Trace the Logic
                </h4>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >04.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      How could this have happened?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    Outcomes are the product of specific rules, incentives, and
                    mechanisms. By thinking in models, we can reverse-engineer
                    the logic of an event to identify the exact factors that
                    allowed a result to emerge.
                  </div>
                </details>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >05.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      What else could be causing this?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    In an interconnected world, the most obvious cause is rarely
                    the only one. This question acts as a control for everyday
                    thinking, training us to look for the hidden factors that
                    simpler explanations overlook.
                  </div>
                </details>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >06.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      Could it be the other way around?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    We often mistake effects for causes. By flipping the script
                    on our assumptions, we can recognize reverse causality and
                    circular reasoning before they lead to faulty conclusions.
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>

              <!-- PART III -->
              <div class="space-y-6">
                <h4
                  class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-6 border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4"
                >
                  Part III: Think Ahead and Think Again
                </h4>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >07.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      What would convince me I’m wrong?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    The ultimate guardrail against bias is falsifiability. By
                    identifying the evidence that would change our minds, we
                    cultivate the intellectual humility required for true
                    analytical rigor.
                  </div>
                </details>

                <details
                  class="group border-b border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10 pb-4 cursor-pointer"
                >
                  <summary
                    class="flex items-center gap-6 list-none hover:text-rust-700 dark:hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span
                      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-charcoal/20 dark:text-softcream/20 group-hover:text-rust-500/40 transition-colors"
                      >08.</span
                    >
                    <h5
                      class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors flex-1"
                    >
                      And then what?
                    </h5>
                    <span
                      class="text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                      >▼</span
                    >
                  </summary>
                  <div
                    class="mt-4 pl-14 md:pl-16 text-sm text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
                  >
                    Strategic thinking requires looking past the immediate fix.
                    This question follows the chain of consequences to uncover
                    the second-order effects and unintended outcomes of any
                    decision or policy.
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
